    <item>
      <title>Using VMware.Sdk.Nsx.Policy: Commands for NSX</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-nsx-policy-cmdlets/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-nsx-policy-cmdlets/</guid>
      <description>
        
          
            <p>VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called <code>VMware.Sdk.Nsx.Policy</code>, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support NSX Policy Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.</p>
<h3 id="connecting-to-a-nsx-instance-with-local-credentials">Connecting to a NSX Instance with Local Credentials</h3>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Start a PowerShell session.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Connect to a NSX instance using local credentials by running the following command:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Connect-NsxServer</span> <span class="n">-Server</span> <span class="nb">sfo-m01</span><span class="n">-nsx01</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">sfo</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span> <span class="n">-User</span> <span class="n">admin</span> <span class="n">-Password</span> <span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span><span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><ol>
<li>Once connected the following information is stored in <code>$defaultNsxConnections</code>.</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 1</span><span class="cl">ServiceUri     : https://sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 2</span><span class="cl">SessionSecret  :
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 3</span><span class="cl">User           : admin
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 4</span><span class="cl">IsConnected    : True
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 5</span><span class="cl">Id             : /NsxServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 6</span><span class="cl">Name           : sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 7</span><span class="cl">Uid            : /NsxServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 8</span><span class="cl">ProductVersion : 9.0.0.0.24705144
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 9</span><span class="cl">ServerUri      : https://sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">10</span><span class="cl">UUID           : /NsxServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@sfo-m01-nsx01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">11</span><span class="cl">Port           : <span class="m">443</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="4">
<li>Disconnect from a NSX instance by running the following command:</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Disconnect-NsxServer</span> <span class="n">-Server</span> <span class="nb">sfo-m01</span><span class="n">-nsx01</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">sfo</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><hr>
<p><strong>NOTE</strong></p>
          
          
        
